Task Overview:
This code implements a button-press task using four lighting patterns across multiple experimental conditions. 

Lighting Patterns:
Participants respond to button lights according to the following rules:
Go-Blue: Press the button when a single blue light appears.
Stop-Red: Do not press when a red light appears.
Only-Blue: When three red lights and one blue light appear, press only the blue button.
Only-Red: When three blue lights and one red light appear, press only the red button.

Conditions (10 trials each):
Go: 10 Go-Blue trials
No-Go: 8 Go-Blue trials AND 2 Stop-Red trials
No-Shift: 10 Only-Blue trials
Shift: 8 Only-Blue trials AND 2 Only-Red trials

Stance Parameters:
Each condition is performed under two stance conditions:
Feet apart
Feet together

Experimental Design:
Each condition × stance combination is presented twice.
Order is randomized within each run.
The full experiment is completed by running the code TWICE, resulting in:
4 conditions × 2 stances × 2 repetitions = 16 total blocks

Summary:
4 conditions
2 stance parameters
10 trials per block
16 total blocks across two runs
